Snap Inc. sank 20 percent in pre-market trading after reporting first-quarter sales and daily active users that missed estimates. The shares are on pace to open near a record intraday low. At least three analysts cut their ratings, as Wall Street laid blame on Snap’s controversial app redesign and said management must act quickly to keep users from fleeing to Facebook Inc.’s Instagram. — With assistance by Jeran Wittenstein, and Arie Shapira